:::summary
Joseph Smith Jr. (1805–1844) was the founding prophet and first president of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints. Latter-day Saints believe he was called of God to restore the fullness of the gospel of Jesus Christ to the earth — including priesthood authority, saving ordinances, and new scripture — after centuries of apostasy.
:::

